data.title: Malawi Population density - data, chart
data.meta_description: Malawi: Population density, people per square km: The latest value from 2021 is 211 people per square km, an increase from 206 people per square km in 2020. In comparison, the world average is 456 people per square km, based on data from 196 countries. Historically, the average for Malawi from 1961 to 2021 is 104 people per square km. The minimum value, 39 people per square km, was reached in 1961 while the maximum of 211 people per square km was recorded in 2021.
